a member of the canadian snowbirds precision 
military flying team was drunk when he crashed his car and died on 
the day he was to perform at an air show authorities said monday 
capt wesley mackay 28 of camrose alberta had an alcohol 
concentration of 0191 percent in his blood said skip rusciewicz 
deputy coroner for westmoreland county pennsylvania law recognizes 
010 as the level of intoxication 
the crash occurred on a private road around 1 am saturday 
police said the snowbirds were to perform 14 hours later 
the pilots are not allowed to consume alcohol within eight hours 
of a flight said col claude thibault commander of canadian 
forces base in moose jaw 
two other team members were injured in the crash 
