that was in the bill reagan vetoed on aug 3 the sources said 
reagan had sought 48 billion for star wars compared to the 
39 billion the program now receives 
approval of a pentagon bill is the major remaining hurdle to be 
cleared before congress finishes work on all 13 appropriations 
bills needed to finance the government starting saturday 
the last time all 13 spending bills were finished by the start 
of the new fiscal year was 1948 
house and senate democratic leaders are pushing to finish the 
bills and avoid giving the gop and vice president george bush a 
potentially embarrassing electionyear issue 
after yearlong budget battles congress sent the president a 
1400page 600 billion catchall spending bill last december 
nearly three months into the present fiscal year 
in reagans state of the union address he threatened to veto 
any similar giant spending bills this year and scores of lawmakers 
signed letters pledging to support him 
this years appropriations work was made easier by the budget 
summit agreement between reagan and congressional leaders last 
november 
that pact settled many broad spending questions for fiscal 1989 
but disputes over various provisions within several individual 
bills have caused delays 
lawmakers have said the dispute over the defense bill was the 
most serious and that its resolution would make it likely that all 
13 bills would be finished on time 
many democrats fear that if congress does not finish its 
appropriations work on time this year the president and 
republicans will use that failure to paint the majority party as 
inefficient and incapable of adhering to budget processes 
reagan has thus far signed four appropriations bills and two 
others have been sent to his desk 
the pentagon spending compromise also drops a restriction added 
by congress on testing of depressedtrajectory missiles a type of 
atomictipped weapon being developed by the pentagon the sources 
said 
the bill provides 300 billion for all pentagon spending the 
same as the earlier bill that would be a slight decrease from the 
current 302 billion pentagon budget 
