institute for alternative agricultural products within the 
agriculture department 
a nonprofit agricultural research commercialization corp also 
would be created that would use loans loan guarantees interest 
subsidies and other means to spur product commercialization 
under the measure 20 million a year through fiscal year 2000 
would be authorized for development of new agricultural products 
15 million to commercialize products and up to 600000 to enhance 
marketing of existing ones 
the bills overall price tag was estimated by the congressional 
budget office at 206 million over five years 
with perhaps three weeks to go before lawmakers adjourn 
however the future of the measure is clouded the senate has 
offered no guarantees that it will get to the measure 
the bill would establish grants for research into statistical 
methods of measuring chemicals and microorganisms in food products 
and means of preventing contamination 
also under the measure an office of groundwater policy 
determination would be established within the agriculture 
department that provision was included at the urging of republican 
rep fred grandy of iowa where concern is growing over findings of 
pesticide contamination in groundwater 
the bill would provide 3 million in each of three years for 
research into aquaculture or fish farming 
