and development of crops used in socalled critical materials the 
measure would set the program at an 8 million level for each of 
the next two years 
most money under that program would go to research into guayule 
a plant grown in the southwest that produces a natural rubber 
that can be used for highperformance aircraft tires 
the bill would enable farmers to plant socalled alternative 
crops in 1989 and 1990 without losing their base acreage listed 
with the department of agriculture the base acreage is used to 
calculate the size of the federal payments they get for producing 
wheat feed grains cotton and rice 
meanwhile the house approved on a voice vote a separate measure 
to establish a 25member commission on the improvement of the 
federal crop insurance program 
ten of the 21 voting members would come from the insurance 
industry and 10 from among agricultural producers with the manager 
of the corporation also serving on the panel the four nonvoting 
members would come from congress 
the goal of the panel would be to recommend changes in the 
program which has lost more than 1 billion since 1980 when a 
major overhaul was approved 
