the number of working americans with wages 
below the poverty level for a family of four increased by more than 
1 million last year according to a new senate report 
the report prepared by the democratic staff of the senate 
budget committee from census bureau data concluded that both 
highpaying and lowpaying jobs have grown at the expense of a 
shrinking middle class over the past eight years 
fueling the debate over the quality of 16 million new jobs since 
president reagan took office the report was immediately criticized 
by senate republicans as misleading and inaccurate 
