defined as those between 11611 and 46444 in 1987 dollars in 
1979 said the report released monday 
between the peak of the business cycle in 1979 and the latest 
year of the current expansion in 1987 only 38 percent of the 
increase in employment was in middle wage jobs it added 
as a result according to the data the share of middlewage 
earners declined from 64 percent to 613 percent between 1979 and 
1987 those earning a poverty wage climbed from 324 percent to 
342 percent and those with high wages more than 46444 rose 
from 37 percent to 45 percent of the working population 
the committees chairman retiring sen lawton chiles dfla 
