opera it was his first met venture into heavier roles than the 
light clear bel canto parts he had been singing one heard strain 
in his voice as he repeatedly sang manrico that season now the 
role sounds natural and totally unstrained 
miss marton was singing leonora at the met for the first time 
her voice is closer to being shrill than soft and sweet but she 
has the volume flexibility and stamina for the part the lastact 
duet with milnes was excitingly sung by both and her damor 
sullali rosee was affecting 
