to weaken organized labor at the bargaining table 
james linsey representing the air line pilots association said 
the layoffs were inconsistent with past eastern practices he said 
they also violated railway labor act requirements to preserve the 
status quo during labor negotiations 
there certainly is past practice to cut unprofitable routes 
said williams 
