nowadays is western music for 11 bars at a time 
under international copyright laws any duplication of at least 
12 bars of existing music is an infringement 
hindi music is the term used to describe songs in films in the 
hindi language in earlier years the films were mostly lyrical 
romances and their soulful songs helped make a movie popular 
but more recent films are more actionoriented pulsing with a 
disco hindilanguage soundtrack whose rhythms are usually taken 
from western hit tunes 
