<TEXT>
a pill that prevents heartworms in jimmy carters 
bird dogs also halts a parasite that blinds thousands of third 
world residents and the former president is helping to make sure 
that it reaches them 
the task force for child survival a public health foundation 
based at the carter presidential center is overseeing a worldwide 
system to get the drug mectizan to the 85 million people at risk 
for the tropical disease 
mectizan is the commercial name for invermectin used by 
veterinarians to treat heartworms in dogs and other parasites in 
cattle and swine 
carter discussed his organizations role in the program in a 
recent telephone interview from his home in plains 
ive got two bird dogs and one of my constant problems is that 
my dogs get heartworms carter said when a mosquito bites a 
dog a little microorganism goes through the body and winds up in 
the dogs heart and causes heartworms 
mectizan is very effective against heartworm not only with 
dogs but with other animals and it also proves to be effective 
against river blindness because river blindness is caused by the 
sting of a little fly that grows in very rapidly flowing streams 
said the former president 
river blindness formally known as onchnocerciasis is caused by 
a parasitic worm spread by the fly it has infected 275 million 
people in more than 30 countries mostly in africa and latin 
america 350000 have been blinded 
one dose of mectizan kills the adult worms millions of tiny 
offspring and prevents the adult from reproducing for a year it is 
the worms offspring called microfilaria that cause the symptoms 
of the disease including skin lesions severe itching and the 
blinding eye lesions 
the medicine halts the progress of the disease but does not 
reverse damage already caused by microfilaria a person bitten by 
the fly who takes mectizan once a year for the eightto12year 
life cycle of the adult worm will be free of the disease unless he 
is reinfected by another fly bite 
mectizan derived from acids produced by a bacterium found in 
japanese soil is manufactured by merck amp co the rahway nj 
pharmaceutical company began developing the drug for humans in 1980 
another heartworm medicine for dogs diethylcarbamazine has 
been found effective in fighting a parasitic disease called 
loiasis prevalent in western and central africa the disease is 
caused by the loa loa or african eyeworm and it is spread by 
biting flies that feed on human blood the disease can cause heart 
and kidney damage 
the world health organization has been fighting river blindness 
for years who and merck spent seven years on research trials 
before mectizan was approved for human use by french drug officials 
last year clearing the way for worldwide distribution 
carter said merck has volunteered to make the drug available 
worldwide and free of charge the company said last year that 
building a distribution network was its only remaining roadblock 
thats where carters organization comes in merck and who said 
they wanted an independent committee of experts to review the 
organizations set up to distribute the drug to monitor any adverse 
reactions and to keep records on the permanent distribution program 
the mectizan expert committee is chaired by dr william h 
foege executive director of the carter center and a former 
director of the us centers for disease control who was 
instrumental in organizing the worldwide smallpox eradication 
program 
next month the committee will begin reviewing the first 
applications for the program clearing the way for merck to start 
shipping the medicine to highrisk areas 
</TEXT>
