<TEXT>
lt gen james a abrahamson the first and 
only director of president reagans star wars research program 
has decided to retire from the military next february the pentagon 
said tuesday 
the 55yearold abrahamson a threestar air force general who 
assumed command of the fledgling strategic defense initiative 
organization in april 1984 will be replaced by air force lt gen 
george l monahan jr said dan howard the pentagons chief 
spokesman 
monahans nomination must be confirmed by the senate 
abrahamson will retire feb 1 after 33 years of active military 
service howard said the general has not announced any future 
plans 
according to documents released tuesday by the pentagon 
including a memo from abrahamson to defense secretary frank c 
carlucci the star wars chief decided on his own early this summer 
to request retirement 
abrahamson said he had concluded the next president should be 
allowed to dictate new policies for star wars development to a new 
leadership team 
i am proud of the people of sdi who have not indulged 
themselves with the negative it cant be done approach to 
problems abrahamson wrote 
however a new administration will undoubtedly have different 
ideas or approaches to sdi therefore i reluctantly have concluded 
that the program will best be served by allowing new leadership to 
represent new policy and direction as you requested i will serve 
until a successful transition is well under way 
the star wars program is an effort to develop lasers and other 
exotic weapons that could be deployed in space and on the ground to 
automatically shoot down soviet nuclear missiles congress 
repeatedly has refused in recent years to fund the program at the 
pace sought by president reagan but nonetheless has allowed the 
research to continue 
abrahamson a former astronaut who never got to fly in space is 
credited with putting together a formal organization to oversee the 
research work which is conducted in laboratories around the world 
while serving as an effective cheer leader to congress and 
the business community 
even in his retirement memo to carlucci abrahamson couldnt 
resist praising the program saying his star wars job had been the 
best of his career and had allowed me to appreciate the daring 
scope of the presidents vision and the genius available to the 
country to solve this and other daunting challenges 
i have great confidence that this initiative will go forward 
and will succeed i will continue to dedicate myself to sdi to my 
last day of active duty and after 
abrahamson a native of williston nd is a vietnam war combat 
pilot who trained as an astronaut for the manned orbiting 
laboratory program before it was canceled in 1969 
in 1981 the general returned to the world of space serving as 
the national aeronautics and space administrations associate 
administrator for the shuttle program he oversaw the first 10 
shuttle launches before returning to the air force and assuming 
command of the star wars effort 
monahan 54 is a native of minneapolis who is one of the air 
forces top procurement officials 
