problem curiel says 
not so in the secure heart of christies curiel who is also an 
executive vice president and director of the firm casually 
interrupts a phone conversation and calls out diane the diamond 
please 
it arrives in dianes hand in a small black box that doesnt fit 
together properly inside it is nestled in a piece of oftenused 
tissue paper 
it took three years beginning in 1985 to cut the diamond from 
the 890carat stone in which it was mined diamond cutters do not 
work by the hour but by the carat 
an artisan jacques swaab began the job he worked for six 
months determining the most economical shape a shield or 
triolette a complicated asymmetrical triangular design more 
than 2 inches long about one and onethird inches wide and a 
fraction over an inch deep curiel who will conduct the auction 
points to a one quarterinch facet and says it probably took a 
month to make that one cut 
the cutting was finished this year by another artisan hy 
kessler and the diamond drew crowds on exhibit at the smithsonian 
institution in washington 
the final product fits easily in the palm of ones hand and 
weighs about as much as a cigarette lighter 
the current owners new york jewelry dealers marvin samuels and 
louis glick in partnership with the zale corp a retail chain 
headquartered in dallas dont explain their reluctance to reveal 
the diamonds origins 
april of this year was a big month for diamonds on april 19 
sothebys auctioned off an 8591carat white diamond for 
9310000 a day later christies sold a 5259carat stone for 
7480000 or a record percarat price of 142000 for a white 
diamond at that price per carat the new diamond would run over 57 
million but as curiel says they cant be compared 
in april 1987 he sold a rare red diamond weighing less than a 
carat for 880000 an alltime percarat record 
some 300 people will witness the auction but the principal 
bidders will probably be absent relying on agents or phoned bids 
understandable they dont like that kind of celebrity people 
following them around trying to sell them something else 
but in all likelihood the buyers name will be made public 
curiel says theres always a chance that the buyers name will 
become eternally linked to the gem its an opportunity for 
immortality 
