<TEXT>
after centuries at the center of a 
tugofwar between germany and france this city nestled on a 
tranquil river now harmonizes french joie de vivre with german 
efficiency 
strasbourg is a symbol says deputy mayor germain muller 
who is in charge of the celebrations marking the citys 2000th 
anniversary this year france and germany which often fought 
over this place are now the countries leading us toward a united 
europe 
pope john paul ii will spend four days beginning oct 8 in 
this city between west germanys black forest and frances vosges 
mountains he will address the entity that symbolizes european 
unity the european parliament which meets in the chambers of the 
