<TEXT>
rising country music performer keith 
whitley says his career is just getting started even though hes 
been singing on the road for 18 years 
the 33yearold singer hit the top of the country music charts 
in august with the single dont close your eyes the album of 
the same name has been in the top 10 
were at the point where all systems are go said whitley 
whose honkytonk style of singing is traditional country music with 
lyrics embracing pain and joy that sounds odd for somebody whos 
been on the road for about 20 years 
he was only 15 when he and friend ricky skaggs a year older 
joined ralph stanleys clinch mountain boys a bluegrass band like 
whitley skaggs eventually became a solo country singer 
whitley then survived his remaining reckless teenage years and 
battled a stubborn drinking problem to become one of country 
musics emerging stars along with randy travis and dwight yoakam 
ive been in this business for a long long time he said in 
an interview but from the musical standpoint and a personal 
standpoint were really just at the beginning of my career 
as a carefree teen in sandy hook ky he bought bootleg 
bourbon poured it down his thirsty throat and then enjoyed 
challenging the rural roads at breathless speeds deep in appalachia 
basically when i was growing up the only thing we did for 
pastime was go to bootleggers and get something to drink and ride 
around and drink it and drive around and see how fast you could 
take those mountain curves he recalled 
at age 17 he was in a car with a companion who attempted to 
round a curve at 120 mph the car wrecked killing his friend 
the doctor told me i came close to breaking my neck said 
whitley who was cut but not hurt in the accident 
at 19 he drove off a 120foot cliff into a frozen river 
escaping with a broken collarbone 
there were a lot more less serious accidents and brushes with 
the law he said 
but always he was intrigued by music he played with stanleys 
band on the weekends as a teenager and later was lead singer for 
jd crowe and the new south a countrybluegrass band 
after earning the reputation as a fine musician and singer he 
moved to nashville in the mid1980s and landed a recording contract 
with rca records his hits besides dont close your eyes 
include miami my amy ten feet away homecoming 63 and 
hard livin 
he quit drinking in 1987 
it was a matter of life and death he said if i hadnt 
stopped drinking i dont think id be alive today i did so many 
crazy things while drinking 
whitley who is married to grand ole opry singer lorrie morgan 
said his lifestyle intensified his music 
not to sound conceited but ive lived breathed and cried 
this music since i was 3 or 4 years old whitley said i take 
it very seriously most of the things i sing in my songs ive 
lived 
i dont wish the others would have to go through that but i 
believe ive got the credentials to sing some of the things i sing 
about where some others dont 
the whole deal with my music has been the emotional quality 
songs i do have to strike an emotional chord the first time i sing 
them its not uncommon for me to get so wrapped up in a song that 
i cry several times when i sing them thats the difference between 
my music and some of the other folks 
his dont close your eyes is about the desperation of love 
people identified with it women seemed to like it and they 
are a big part of the recordbuying public at shows people often 
come up to me and say they feel like it was written about them 
the melody is real mournful you can get lost emotionally 
singing it 
one of the songs on the album is i never go around mirrors 
a hit years ago by the late country star lefty frizzell 
whitley had a verse added to the song a few hours before he 
recorded it he visited frizzells grave and wept 
that sounds weird to people but his music was very important 
to me growing up whitley said people dont understand why i did 
that but it meant a lot to me 
</TEXT>
